10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Audit</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Often, if you are marketing an investment, it =
helps to have your thing validated by some trusted third party. If you=E2=
=80=99ve got a company and you want investors, it=E2=80=99s good to send th=
em financial statements that have been audited by a well-known accounting f=
irm. If you=E2=80=99re selling bonds, it=E2=80=99s good to have a high cred=
it rating from a recognized ratings firm. If you=E2=80=99re a software comp=
any, it is good to have a security audit from a reputable firm.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are running a scam, all of=C2=A0this is=
 also true, maybe even more so: If you=E2=80=99re selling a fake thing, it =
is very helpful for you to say =E2=80=9Cthis thing has been certified by a =
trusted third party.=E2=80=9D But of course that is hard, because the reaso=
n the trusted third parties are trusted is because they are in the business=
 of=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>certifying scams, so they are unlikely to certif=
y you.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are ways, of course. Perhaps if you are =
clever you can deceive the auditors into certifying your financial statemen=
ts. Perhaps you can bribe them. Perhaps you can hire (or set up) some shady=
 fake auditor and give it a trusted-sounding name. Maybe your financial sta=
tements were audited by KMPG and your bonds are rated AAA by Moodie=E2=80=
=99s Investors Service.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An approach that I had not really thought of i=
s:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Go to a real, well-regarded, trusted =
auditing firm.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Ask them to audit y=
our thing.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">They conduct the audit =
and send you back a letter being like =E2=80=9Cno, see, this is actually a=
=C2=A0scam.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You go around=
 to investors saying =E2=80=9Cyou can trust us because we were audited by t=
he good firm!=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The investo=
rs are like =E2=80=9Cah well anyone audited by that firm must be fine=E2=80=
=9D and give you their money.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Technically, I think, =E2=80=9Cwe were audited=
 by X=E2=80=9D just means that they=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>the audited, not=
 that you=C2=A0<em>passed</em>.=C2=A0It=E2=80=99s maybe=C2=A0true? And yet =
misleading? Also seems not that helpful: A sophisticated investor would pro=
bably say =E2=80=9Cah right let=E2=80=99s see the audit report,=E2=80=9D wh=
ile an unsophisticated one probably wouldn=E2=80=99t care, or recognize the=
 auditing firm=E2=80=99s name. Still. It helps with the patter; it gives th=
ings the ring of truth.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s a <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34110962.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly9zZWN1cml0aWVz=
LmNvbG9yYWRvLmdvdi9wcmVzcy1yZWxlYXNlL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UtY29sb3JhZG8tc2VjdXJ=
pdGllcy1jb21taXNzaW9uZXItZmlsZXMtY29tcGxhaW50LWFnYWluc3QtYWxsZWdlZA/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB68db49b0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Colorado Securities Commission fraud c=
ase</a> against a pastor named Eli Regalado and his wife Kaitlyn, who start=
ed a crypto thing called INDXcoin, and a crypto exchange called Kingdom Wea=
lth Exchange to trade it. Standard stuff, you know, God told them to sell c=
rypto, etc.:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the complaint filed by the Colora=
do Attorney General=E2=80=99s Office, investigators from the Colorado Divis=
ion of Securities found that from June 2022 to April 2023, INDXcoin raised =
nearly $3.2 million from more than 300 individuals. The complaint alleges t=
hat Regalado targeted Christian communities in Denver and claimed that God =
told him directly that investors would become wealthy if they put money int=
o INDXcoin. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Regalados allegedly continued to promote t=
he INDXcoin as a low risk, high profit investment.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The complaint alleges that in reality, the IND=
Xcoin was illiquid and practically worthless; investors lost millions; and =
Defendants dissipated investor funds to support their lavish lifestyle.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, the appeal to a trusted third-party aut=
hority (God). Plus some bizarre claims about the mechanics of the crypto th=
ing; from <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34110962=
.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly9kcml2ZS5nb29nbGUuY29tL2ZpbGUvZC8xd1NkZDRzQnVGa1h6MmNySTR=
ibUN3Y3lwa0VZWXVBNjYvdmlldw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB116dabbd" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the=
 complaint</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The =E2=80=9CINDXcoin, as describe=
d by Defendants in the Whitepaper, is purportedly an =E2=80=9Cindex-based c=
ryptocurrency that tracks and indexes the value of the top one hundred cryp=
tocurrencies (ranked by market cap) through an AI-based data procurement me=
chanism sourced from multiple data points to ensure accuracy.=E2=80=9D</p><=
/blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nooo.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foot=
note-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !=
important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;=
">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Defendants persuaded investors tha=
t the INDXcoin was uniquely situated to provide its holders with big return=
s. Defendants explained that INDXcoin was designed to be =E2=80=9Ca less vo=
latile and risky coin to hold...with less exposure to the risks associated =
with single coin offerings.=E2=80=9D Defendants said INDXcoin was =E2=80=9C=
immune to investors =E2=80=98pumping and dumping=E2=80=99 cryptocurrency th=
rough a coordinated liquidation event,=E2=80=9D as the value of the INDXcoi=
n was pegged to =E2=80=9Cthe overall momentum of the crypto market.=E2=80=
=9D Defendants=E2=80=99 future plans would only provide more assurance to c=
oin holders, acting to =E2=80=9Csolidify INDXcoin=E2=80=99s global value, a=
cting as the first line of defense against exchange-specific price volatili=
ty if a large portfolio holding INDXcoin is liquidated on an exchange.=E2=
=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Whatever. But for some reason they decided to =
go to a crypto=C2=A0auditing firm called Hacken, <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34110962.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly9oYWNrZW4uaW8vYXVk=
aXRzLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB46de1379" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> whose website</a> tells=
 me that they have done smart contract audits for crypto things including B=
inance. =E2=80=9CDefendants touted the safety of INDXcoin and the KWE by te=
lling investors that the coin and the exchange had undergone a rigorous aud=
it.=E2=80=9D How=E2=80=99d the audit go?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The auditor, Hacken, told Defendants their pro=
ducts=E2=80=99 =E2=80=9Csecurity score=E2=80=9D was zero out of ten. Additi=
onally, wrote Hacken, =E2=80=9C[c]onsidering all metrics, the total score o=
f the report is 0 out of 10.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the Hacken report, =E2=80=9C[w]he=
n proof-of-stake mining is enabled, value of reward in coinbase is not vali=
dated which allows to generate any number of new coins...In practice, it al=
lows to generate an infinite number of new coins.=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To the extent that Hacken could evaluate Defen=
dants=E2=80=99 code, Hacken highlighted that the code submitted by Defendan=
ts contained changes that =E2=80=9Cdid not=C2=A0align with the standards up=
held by Bitcoin Core,=E2=80=9D and contained transcription errors that lead=
 to =E2=80=9Cnumerous critical issues.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Seems bad! And yet also good marketing:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">However, upon receiving the Hacken Report, Def=
endants posted in the KWE Community Forum the =E2=80=9CBREAKING NEWS=E2=80=
=9D that =E2=80=9CINDXcoin has been proofed by Hacken! The toughest, most l=
egit crypto audit in the world! And before we launch! We are so far ahead o=
f 90% of the cryptos that have existed for years!=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nowhere in the post did Defendants disclose th=
at the results of the Hacken Report reflected that Defendants=E2=80=99 prod=
ucts were catastrophically technologically deficient.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway I have been quoting the Colorado compla=
int, these are just allegations, etc., but <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/34110962.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY29pbmRlc2suY29tL3=
BvbGljeS8yMDI0LzAxLzIzL2xvcmQteW91LXRvbGQtbWUtdG8tZG8tdGhpcy1wYXN0b3ItZGVmZ=
W5kcy10YWtpbmctMTNtLWZyb20tZmFpbGVkLWNyeXB0by8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB202=
cea65" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> Coindesk reports</a> on Eli Regalado=E2=80=99s magnificent=
=C2=A0response to the charges:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The pastor =E2=80=93 who had worked in digital=
 marketing =E2=80=93 responded in a video message posted on the project's w=
ebsite, sharing a sentiment that's unusual from a crypto founder cornered b=
y government authorities: "Those charges are true."</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"We sold a cryptocurrency with no clear exit,"=
 he said, explaining that God told him to build it and give investors ten t=
imes the money they put in. "We did. We took God at his word."</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"The Lord told us to walk away from our parkin=
g company. ... He took us into this cryptocurrency ... well, that cryptocur=
rency turned out to be a scam.... And I said Lord ... you told me to do thi=
s," he said in the video.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The couple also took about $1.3 million from m=
ore than $3 million raised for the project. Regalado said about $500,000 we=
nt to the Internal Revenue Service, and a "few hundred thousand" was devote=
d to a home remodeling project that "the Lord told us to do."</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well right but you said that about Hacken too.=
 I think I will need a bit more proof for the claim =E2=80=9CGod told us to=
 do some scams and also remodel our kitchen.=E2=80=9D</p>
